/wiki/Paola_Espinosa: Paola Milagros Espinosa Sánchez (born 31 July 1985) is a Mexican diver and represented Mexico at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens, the 2008 Summer Olympics in Beijing, where she was her national team's flagbearer, and the 2012 Summer Olympics in London.
/wiki/Diving_at_the_2011_Summer_Universi: Diving will be contested at the 2011 Summer Universiade from August 16 to August 22 at the Shenzhen Swimming and Diving Gym in Shenzhen, China. Men's and women's 1 and 3 metre springboard, 10 metre platform, synchronized 3 and 10 metre platform, and team events will be held.
/wiki/Rommel_Pacheco: Rommel Agmed Pacheco Manrufo (born 12 July 1986) is a Mexican diver. He was the gold medalist in the 10-meter platform at the 2003 Pan American Games. In the 2004 Summer Olympics he finished in 10th place in the 10-meter platform and 3-meter springboard. In the 2008 Summer Olympics he finished in 8th place in the 10-meter platform.
/wiki/Juli\u00e1n_S\u00e1nchez_(diver): Julián Isaac Sánchez Gallegos (born 22 August 1988 in Mexico City) is a Mexican diver. He won one gold and one silver medal in the 2011 Pan-American Games. He competed at the 2012 Summer Olympics in the men's synchronised springboard diving, with Yahel Castillo, finishing in 7th place.
/wiki/Angel_Ramirez: The Barrio Boyzz were a Latin pop group. The group was made up of Puerto Ricans who grew up in New York City. They gained popularity during the 1990s,  when they became label-mates with the landed their first Billboard number-one song entitled "Donde Quiera Que Estés" (Where Ever You Are) in 1993, from the album of the same name.
/wiki/Archery_at_the_2011_Summer_Univers: Archery will be contested at the 2011 Summer Universiade from August 14 to August 18 at Football Pitch One and Football Pitch Two of Shenwanyi Road in Shenzhen, China. Men's and women's individual and men's, women's, and mixed team events will be held using the recurve bow and the compound bow, with one set of events for each type of bow.
/wiki/Tatiana_Ortiz: Tatiana Ortiz Galicia (born January 12, 1984 in Mexico City) is an athlete from Mexico. She competes in diving and represented Mexico at the 2008 Summer Olympics in Beijing, where she won a bronze medal in the 10m Synchronized Platform with Paola Espinosa.
/wiki/Monica_Patricia_Dominguez_Lara: Monica Patricia Dominguez Lara (born (1988-03-05)5 March 1988) is a Mexican female weightlifter, competing in the 58 kg category and representing Mexico at international competitions.
/wiki/Weightlifting_at_the_2011_Summer_U: Weightlifting was contested at the 2011 Summer Universiade from August 13 to August 18 at the Comprehensive Training Hall and the Weightlifting Training Hall in Shenzhen Sport School in Shenzhen, China. Men's and women's individual and team events were held.
/wiki/Taekwondo_at_the_2011_Summer_Unive: Taekwondo was contested at the 2011 Summer Universiade from August 18 to August 23 at the No. 6, No. 7, and No. 8 Pavilions at the Shenzhen Conference and Exhibition Center in Shenzhen, China.
/wiki/Gerardo_Garc\u00eda: Gerardo García León (born 7 December 1974), known simply as Gerardo, is a Spanish retired footballer, and the manager of EDF Logroño women's team. A defender of wide range, he operated on the right flank.
/wiki/Idulio_Islas: Idulio Islas Gómez (born January 16, 1987 in Morelos) is a Mexican taekwondo practitioner. He won a silver medal for the 68 kg division at the 2009 World Taekwondo Championships in Copenhagen, Denmark, and bronze at the 2011 Summer Universiade in Shenzhen, China.
/wiki/Itzel_Manjarrez: Itzel Adilene Manjarrez Bastidas (born 10 April 1990) is a Mexican taekwondo athlete.
/wiki/Rodolfo_Cazaub\u00f3n: Rodolfo Cazaubón Jr. (born 5 August 1989) is a Mexican professional golfer who currently plays on the Web.com Tour.
/wiki/Carlos_Ortiz_(golfer): Carlos Ortiz (born 24 April 1991) is a Mexican professional golfer who has played on the PGA Tour and Web.com Tour.
/wiki/Golf_at_the_2011_Summer_Universiad: Golf was contested at the 2011 Summer Universiade from 17–20 August at the Mission Hills Golf Club in Shenzhen, China. Men's and women's individual and team events were held.
/wiki/Valeria_Pulido: Valeria Pulido Velasco (born 1 January 1990) is a former professional tennis player from Mexico.
/wiki/Tennis_at_the_2011_Summer_Universi: Tennis was contested at the 2011 Summer Universiade from August 14 to August 21 at the Longgang Tennis Center and the Shenzhen Tennis Center in Shenzhen, China. Men's and women's singles, men's and women's team, and men's, women's, and mixed doubles events were contested.
The women's doubles tennis event at the 2011 Summer Universiade was held from August 14–20 at the Longgang Tennis Center and the Shenzhen Tennis Center in Shenzhen, China.
/wiki/Mexico_at_the_2011_Summer_Universi: Mexico competed at the 2011 Summer Universiade in Shenzhen, China.
